Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.77,0:00:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year 6 CE,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.65,0:00:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a fire devastated Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.94,0:00:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In response,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.36,0:00:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor Augustus did something\Nthat had never been done before
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in the history of the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.16,0:00:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He created a permanent\Nteam of firefighters
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.29,0:00:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who used buckets just like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.17,0:00:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Augustus understood that individuals alone\Ncan't protect themselves from fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.84,0:00:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They need help from the community.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.05,0:00:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When one person's house is on fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.72,0:00:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that creates a risk\Nfor everyone else's homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.98,0:00:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what we've had these last few years\Nis like a horrific global fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.36,0:00:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The COVID pandemic has killed millions\Nand upended economies,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want to stop that\Nfrom happening again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.49,0:01:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,COVID, it's hard to overstate\Nhow awful it's been.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.08,0:01:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's increased the health inequities\Nbetween the rich and the poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.13,0:01:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Survival depended partly\Non your income, your race,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.72,0:01:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the neighborhood you lived in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.97,0:01:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we should seize this opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.80,0:01:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to create a world\Nwhere everyone has a chance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.64,0:01:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to live a healthy and productive life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.27,0:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Also a life free from the fear\Nof the next COVID-19.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.52,0:01:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was on this stage in 2015,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.57,0:01:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one of many people who said
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.49,0:01:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we weren't ready\Nand we needed to get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.16,0:01:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.33,0:01:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The speech actually was watched\Nby a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.91,0:01:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But 90 percent of the views\Nwere after it was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.79,0:01:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,(Laughter)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.71,0:01:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I hope the need is clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.14,0:02:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we've learned a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.01,0:02:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,During this pandemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of things worked well,\Na lot of things didn't work well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.52,0:02:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have all that knowledge\Nto build a prevention system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.73,0:02:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,COVID-19 can be the last pandemic\Nif we take the right steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.82,0:02:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So how, what are these steps?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.37,0:02:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go back\Nand look at what the Romans did.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.04,0:02:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about how, over time,\Nwe've gotten good at preventing big fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.80,0:02:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire prevention is kind of\Nthis pervasive thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.34,0:02:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's well funded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.72,0:02:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's well understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.30,0:02:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If an alarm went off right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.47,0:02:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone here would know\Nwe're supposed to calmly gather,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.01,0:02:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,go out and wait instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.60,0:02:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd know that help would be on the way
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because we have lots of trained\Nfirefighters who practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.82,0:02:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States alone has 370,000\Nfull-time firefighters,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.95,0:03:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,even more than I guessed\Nthat number would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.95,0:03:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have access to water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.79,0:03:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States, for example,\Nhas almost nine million fire hydrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.42,0:03:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that type of investment,\Nthat type of practice,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.54,0:03:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that type of system\Nis what we need to stop pandemics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.18,0:03:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, often in movies,\Nwe'll have pandemics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.60,0:03:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm always impressed\Nwith what takes place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.85,0:03:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at an example\Nof this rapid response.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.81,0:03:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[Motaba River Valley, Zaire]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.56,0:03:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,(Helicopter rotors whirring)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.16,0:03:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's quite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.83,0:03:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need the music,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.00,0:03:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but otherwise we saw\Nexactly what should happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.83,0:03:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,An outbreak’s detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Very quickly, literally within days,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:03:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,doctors are dispatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.76,0:04:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a helicopter\Nto get into exactly ground zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They go in there,\Nand they’ve got the right tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is what should happen\Nwhen an outbreak is spotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.73,0:04:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't have that team,\Nwe don't have those resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.15,0:04:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And if an outbreak took place\Nin a low-income country,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it could be literally months
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.65,0:04:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,before we started to orchestrate\Nthose resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.95,0:04:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So despite what you see in movies,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.41,0:04:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no group of experts\Nstanding by to prevent this disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.21,0:04:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to create a new team.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe we should create\Nwhat I call the GERM team.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.67,0:04:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Germ stands for Global Epidemic\NResponse and Mobilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This group is full-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Their only priority\Nis pandemic prevention.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.93,0:04:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's made up of a diverse\Nset of specialists
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.44,0:04:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with a lot of different\Nrealms of expertise:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.69,0:05:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,epidemiologists, data scientists,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.19,0:05:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,logistics experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.90,0:05:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not just scientific\Nand medical knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.36,0:05:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They also have to have communication\Nand diplomacy skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The cost of this team is significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.83,0:05:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over a billion a year
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to support the 3,000 people\Nwho would be on this team.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.75,0:05:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And its mission is to stop outbreaks\Nbefore they become pandemics.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The work would be coordinated by the WHO.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd be present in many\Nlocations around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.89,0:05:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,stationed in public health agencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd work closely\Nwith the national teams,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.81,0:05:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the income level.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.31,0:05:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd have more\Nin the lower-income countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.98,0:05:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, for example,\Nwe could have GERM members
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.28,0:05:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,say an epidemiologist, working\Nout of the Africa CDC office in Abuja.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And a very important thing\Nis that like firefighters,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.71,0:06:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a GERM team would do drills.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When you want to have quick response,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.30,0:06:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when you want to make sure\Nyou have all the pieces there
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.22,0:06:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can move very quickly,\Npractice is key.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.30,0:06:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you make sure\Neveryone knows what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this team, there could be periods\Nwhere there's no risky outbreak
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they can keep their skills strong
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by working on some\Nof the other infectious diseases,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but that would be a second priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They would work with countries\Nto strengthen their health systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.58,0:06:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The health systems are the front line.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.87,0:06:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to know if, say,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.46,0:06:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of people show up\Nwith a new kind of cough,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s when GERM needs to look into it\Nand say, is this an outbreak?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.13,0:06:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a new pathogen here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the sequence of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so for all of this,\Nthe first 100 days are key.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:06:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Viruses spread exponentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.94,0:07:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if you get in there\Nwhen the infection rate is fairly small,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.52,0:07:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you can actually stop the spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.40,0:07:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, in this epidemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.70,0:07:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,if we'd been able to stop it\Nwithin 100 days,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we would have saved\Nover 98 percent of the lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.12,0:07:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we did have countries\Nthat did a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Australia is an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.25,0:07:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They orchestrated diagnostic capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.46,0:07:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They came up with distancing policies\Nand quarantine policies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.84,0:07:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so their overall death rate\Nper capita will be well less
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.30,0:07:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,than a 10th of other countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.68,0:07:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But we did not, as a world, contain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.48,0:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what we have to do next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.90,0:07:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When COVID struck,\Nwe were almost like Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.52,0:07:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before they had\Nfire buckets and firefighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.61,0:07:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't have the people,\Nthe systems or the tools we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.11,0:07:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with the right investments,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.70,0:07:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we can have a whole new\Ngeneration of tools,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.33,0:08:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,better diagnostics,\Ntherapeutics and vaccines.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.12,0:08:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A good example in the diagnostic area\Nis this little machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.46,0:08:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this is called the Lumira.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.42,0:08:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We can have these all over the world\Nthat can test for any number of diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a 10th as expensive as PCR,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.14,0:08:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s absolutely as accurate,\Nand it’s simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.43,0:08:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So it can be used anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.39,0:08:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We need other R&D investments.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One that I'm very excited\Nabout is the idea of a drug
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.40,0:08:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that you inhale that blocks you\Nfrom getting infected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be pathogen-independent\Nand trigger your immune system
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you'll be protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.32,0:08:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of the tools, the diagnostic tools
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.91,0:08:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and those infection-blocking\Ntools are important
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because they can be staged in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.46,0:08:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we also need vaccines,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.21,0:08:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but we want to stop the outbreak
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.59,0:08:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,before we have to do\Na global vaccination campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.72,0:08:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And so vaccines can play\Na couple of different roles,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but not the primary role.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.97,0:08:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to invest in more than just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.47,0:09:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at vaccines,\Nthey were the miracle of this epidemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They saved millions of lives,\Nbut they can be far better.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to invent\Neasier-to-deliver vaccines
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.82,0:09:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that are just a patch you put on your arm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or something that you inhale.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.28,0:09:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We need vaccines that actually\Nblock infections.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, there were lots\Nof breakthrough infections.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.25,0:09:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We need vaccines that are broad spectrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.71,0:09:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so they work against most\Nof the emerging variants,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which we did not have this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And we also need factories\Nthat are standing by
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.13,0:09:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can build enough vaccines\Nfor the entire world
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.88,0:09:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,within six months
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and achieve far better equity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.06,0:09:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The vaccines can also do something\Nthat would be super helpful,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.77,0:09:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which is to help us eradicate\Nentire families of viruses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Innovative new vaccines used properly\Ncould get rid of the flu family,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.57,0:09:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the coronavirus family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:09:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a huge burden of those,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.61,0:09:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even in non-pandemic years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we get rid of it,\Nit can never cause a pandemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm talking about investments\Nin three broad areas:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.71,0:10:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Disease monitoring,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.17,0:10:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that's GERM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The R and D tools that are far better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, and the most expensive,\Nis improved health systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.05,0:10:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This won't be cheap, but it'll save lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.68,0:10:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And even it'll save money in the long run.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like an insurance policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.10,0:10:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The cost to prevent the next pandemic\Nwill be tens of billions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's compare that\Nto what we just went through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.44,0:10:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The IMF estimates that COVID\Nhas cost nearly 14 trillion dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.49,0:10:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we need to spend billions\Nin order to save trillions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.21,0:10:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the best part of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.25,0:10:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when we're not having an outbreak,\Nthese investments like the Lumira,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.46,0:10:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,those new vaccines,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.34,0:10:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they will make people healthier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.89,0:11:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll shrink the gap,\Nthe health equity gap,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which is gigantic,\Nbetween rich and poor countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.14,0:11:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, we can detect more HIV cases\Nand do a better job of treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.32,0:11:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We can reduce deaths from malaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We can get more people high-quality care.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this is not just a downer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.12,0:11:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about how to stop things\Nfrom getting worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.45,0:11:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but also a chance to make things better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.50,0:11:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If we take the right steps,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.50,0:11:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we can make COVID-19 the last pandemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.92,0:11:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can build a healthier,\Nmore equitable world for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.26,0:11:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.43,0:11:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(Applause)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Helen Walters: Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.28,0:12:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a few follow-up questions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.95,0:12:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and one is really\Nabout the formal status of GERM.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.95,0:12:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So you mentioned this would\Ncost a billion dollars,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.49,0:12:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you mentioned it comes through the WHO,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but exactly who's running this,\Nhow does this work,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.79,0:12:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,how do we make this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.92,0:12:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,BG: Well, GERM does not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.21,0:12:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a proposal I'm putting forward\Nthat hopefully over the next year,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,while the pain of the pandemic\Nis still clear in people's minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.89,0:12:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,will get a global consensus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.43,0:12:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The rich-world governments\Nwill have to step up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.68,0:12:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,like they do with all the aid things\Nand come up with that money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the personnel systems works,\Nso that it's under WHO,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but a really top-notch team,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.52,0:12:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there will be a lot of debate\Nabout how to do that well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, I'm putting it forward
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.99,0:12:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopefully within the next year\Nwe'll get that consensus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.41,0:12:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,HW: Who do you need to pick that up next?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.45,0:12:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,BG: Well, it's really\Nthe rich-world governments.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The WHO has this big yearly meeting,\Nthe World Health Assembly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.00,0:12:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and at some point somebody\Nwill put forward a resolution
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.67,0:13:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll see if the extra resources\Ncan be put in for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.47,0:13:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War II, we did a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.18,0:13:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we created the United Nations,\Nwe talked a lot about war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd be stunned, although, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.35,0:13:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so far the action has been less\Nthan I would have expected,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.73,0:13:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be stunned if we don't go forward\Nwith something pretty close
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to what I'm laying out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.15,0:13:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,HW: This has been pretty personal for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the anti-vaxxers\Nare out there, they are loud,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and this has become personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.79,0:13:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to ask, like,\Nhow are you managing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.33,0:13:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,BG: Well, it's kind of weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.54,0:13:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,(Laughter)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,(Applause)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, our foundation, the Gates Foundation,\Nis very involved in vaccines,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.76,0:13:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the invention of new vaccines,\Nfunding vaccines.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:13:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're very proud that through\Njoint efforts like GAVI,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.43,0:13:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that saved tens of millions of lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's somewhat ironic to have somebody\Nturn around and say, no, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we're using vaccines to kill people\Nor to make money or, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we started the pandemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.61,0:14:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,even some strange things like,\Nthat I somehow want to track, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.57,0:14:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the location of individuals
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.58,0:14:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm so deeply desirous\Nto know where everybody is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(Laughter)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.96,0:14:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure what I'm going to do\Nwith that information.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.79,0:14:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,(Laughter)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.67,0:14:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, does this turn into\Nsomething where, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there's constantly\Ncrazy people showing up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.76,0:14:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.51,0:14:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, hopefully,\Nas the pandemic calms down,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.47,0:14:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,people are more rational about, hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,vaccines are a miracle\Nand there's a lot more we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,HW: So the future is\Nin our hands in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Gates, thank you\Nso much for being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.19,0:14:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,BG: Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,(Applause)
